docs.text: after a hiatus of about fifteen years , the disaster movie has come back with renewed zest .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in early 1997 , there were no less than three movies about volcanoes alone , one on television and two in the theaters , with dante's peak and volcano in heavy competition for the moviegoing dollar .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: of the two , i had heard that dante's peak was the better film , so i decided to check it out when it was released on video .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film begins with a slow motion scene of people in a third world country trying to evacuate their little town .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the town is being covered in ash and sulfuric water from what we presume is a volcanic eruption .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: flaming rocks of various sizes also fall from the sky , crushing homes and people .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: we see people panicking , people crying , and even horses rearing .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is a disaster of biblical proportions , signified to us by one person dragging a cross down a road .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: symbolism doesn't get much more blatant than that .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: we learn that harry dalton ( pierce brosnan ) , a volcanologist with the u . s . geological survey , was there with his wife when the eruption occurred .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: harry survived , but his wife did not .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a few years later , harry is sent to investigate some unusual seismic activity detected near the small town of dante's peak , washington ( which , we are told , has been voted second most desirable place to live ( under 20 , 000 ) by the readers of money magazine ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there harry meets rachel wando , a single mother of two who serves as mayor of dante's peak and proprietor of a small coffee shop .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: although the mayor doesn't seem to be alarmed by the presence of a man sent to determine if the mountain next to their town is going to blow up , a few members of the city council are .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they are afraid that harry's presence is going to scare off an investor who has pledged to put millions of dollars into developing dante's peak .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they would rather have any news of possible stirrings within the neighboring dormant volcano swept under the rug .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , when an amorous young couple takes a skinny-dip in the local hot springs , they turn up cooked by lava which bubbles up from a small fissure underneath .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: thus begins a chain of events leading up to the inevitable eruption .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this film contains a number of cliches .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the amorous couple is one .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as soon as they doff their clothes , you know they're going to die .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the town busybody and the abrasive mother-in-law make appearances , as does the death-defying dog .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: countless familiar scenarios only serve to make this film very predictable .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: watching the movie , i was able to not only anticipate each of the major plot elements , but some of the dialogue as well .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: unfortunate , since much of the dialog is terrible .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for example , harry's boss , paul ( charles hallahan ) , and a team from the u . s . geological survey join harry to assess the situation .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: paul basically tells the townsfolk that harry's eruption predictions aren't cause for alarm .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this causes harry to leave in a fit of rage , only to turn up the next day , ready for work .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when paul asks harry why he stayed , he says with grim determination , " cause this town's in trouble and i'm the best man you've got . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: even better is when harry is trying to explain the need to jolt the residents into leaving .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he likens the situation to how a frog will jump out if dropped into a pot of boiling water .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if the frog is in cold water which is gradually heated up , however , the frog won't move and will allow itself to be cooked .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " is that your recipe for frog soup ? "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: asks one of the team members .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " it's my recipe for disaster , " responds harry .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: dante's peak has a singular talent for pointing out the obvious .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: our heroes are in a boat in the middle of a lake which harry realizes the volcanic activity has turned to acid .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mayor wando demonstrates her brilliant powers of deduction by proclaiming , in a very grave tone , " acid eats metal . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: thanks for the tip .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when we first see the u . s . geological survey building , there's a caption labeling it as such .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this wouldn't have been so bad if it weren't for the fact that the caption is right above a sign on the building which reads , in large letters , " u . s . geological survey . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i suppose the caption is for people who can't read signs .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: although harry and mayor wando become an item by the end of the film , the viewer has no idea why .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is a severe lack of chemistry between the two characters , and the relationship seems rushed because of this .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when they get close to kissing , i was asking myself , " why do they want to kiss ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: were they even attracted to each other ? "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if i were the mayor , i would sure think twice about kissing a guy who doesn't even crack a smile through the whole movie , trying to pull off the rough-yet-debonair act .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: who does he think he is ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: james bond ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the eruption of the volcano feels similarly rushed .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there are several " warning signs " prior to the eruption itself , but they are so lackluster and without suspense that we don't feel as if they are leading up to anything .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for example , one of the survey team members makes his way down into the crater of the volcano in order to retrieve a remote controlled robot .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a tremor occurs .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: does he plunge headlong to his death ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: is he engulfed in lava which shoots up from below ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: no , a couple of rocks fall on him and break his leg .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the sole purpose of this scene seemed to be to set up the subsequent chopper rescue scene , which i suppose was intended to be dramatic as well .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it wasn't .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: one plot thread left noticeably hanging was the investment in the town of dante's peak .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in a disaster movie , there's usually one guy who's greedy enough to cover up the possibility of eruption/fire/earthquake/explosion/tsunami/tornado/meteorite , and usually gets killed by the disaster .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's okay , of course , because we all think he got what he deserved .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if you're going to be unoriginal , you might as well go all the way .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in dante's peak , the city councilmembers are concerned , but they don't really try hard enough .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: maybe the mayor's abrasive mother-in-law should have been the one .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for no apparent reason , she snaps at harry for even positing that the volcano could erupt .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: perhaps her ancestors invested in some pompeii real estate .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there are a couple of good things about this movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the first is the scenery .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there are panoramic shots of forests , lakes and mountains that are absolutely beautiful .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the second is the special effects .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they are the closest i've ever seen to a real pyroclastic eruption .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but when elements which don't speak are going to be the best parts of your movie , you'd probably better rewrite the script .
